      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the iconic S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six engine. This high-revving power plant utilizes individual throttle bodies and high-pressure Double VANOS variable valve timing to produce a linear 333 hp with an 8,000 RPM redline. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual gearbox and an M-Variable locking differential. This example is mechanically sound, having undergone a recent Inspection II service and a proactive rear subframe reinforcement to ensure chassis rigidity. The suspension remains taut, and the hydraulic steering rack provides the unfiltered feedback characteristic of this era of M-division engineering. A well-sorted driver\u2019s car for the serious enthusiast.",
